      </memberdef>
    </sectiondef>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Task descriptor for the cooperative scheduler. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Defines the task control block (<ref refid="structSYN__Task" kindref="compound">SYN_Task</ref>) that pairs a protothread with scheduling metadata: priority, state, name, and delay target.</para>
<para>Tasks are caller-owned — you allocate them however you like (static array, global, on the stack). The scheduler just takes a pointer to your array. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
